@bignimbus sorry for the late reply, I am aware of the configuration that should be added to the bundler, in my case I am using a create-react-app boilerplate, I got around configuring it to import from graphql files without ejecting the CRA by using a package called `graphql.macro`

First I import the loader and pass the path of the query/fragment to it
```ts
import { loader } from 'graphql.macro'

const PRODUCTS = loader('../graphql/queries/products.graphql')
```

and here is an example on how I used it with apollo cache
```ts
await createProductMutation({
  variables: {
    data: {
      name: values.name,
      make: values.make,
      type: values.type,
      description: values.description,
      category: values.category
        ? { connect: { id: values.category } }
        : undefined,
      purchasePrice: values.purchasePrice,
      price: values.price,
      wholesalePrice: values.wholesalePrice,
      halfWholesalePrice: values.halfWholesalePrice,
    }
  },
  update: (cache, { data }) => {
    const newProduct = data?.createOneProduct;
    const existingProducts = cache.readQuery({
      query: PRODUCTS,
    }) as any

    cache.writeQuery({
      query: PRODUCTS,
      data: {
        products: [...existingProducts.products, newProduct]
      }
    })
  }
});
```

Works like a charm, thank you for your help!
PS: I am using `typescript-react-apollo` generated hooks from the guild's codegen https://the-guild.dev/graphql/codegen

